data.speaker: NPC
data.stableText: Not yet, Orlando.
data.fragmentedText: Not yet—no. Not without it.
data.ghostlyText: Not yet. Come back with the proof, not just the wanting.

data.speaker: NPC
data.stableText: The parchment—The Knole Property Act. The deed that lets me name an heir to Knole House. Without it, it’s only talk.
data.fragmentedText: The parchment. The Knole Act—the deed. Without it I can’t name you. Bring it.
data.ghostlyText: The parchment that makes a house obey. Knole won’t open its doors to your name without my seal. Bring it.

data.speaker: NPC
data.stableText: Go—find it. Then return, and we’ll speak like adults: whether I keep you close… or send you away empty-handed.
data.fragmentedText: Go. Find it. Then come back. Then I decide. Not before.
data.ghostlyText: Go. Fetch it. Then we can decide if you become family… or a footnote.

data.speaker: NPC
data.stableText:
There you are.
That paper isn’t romance, Orlando—it’s law. It’s the Act that tells England who may inherit Knole: the great house, the land, the name.
Give it here. One press of my seal and I can bind Knole to you… or lock it away from you forever.
But before I turn ink into fate, I will look at you once more.
data.fragmentedText:
There. The paper—good.
It’s law, not a love letter. It decides who may inherit Knole—house, land, name.
Give it. One seal and Knole remembers you… or doesn’t.
Stand still. Let me see what I’m about to create.
data.ghostlyText:
You brought the paper.
It isn’t a charm. It’s law: the words that decide who Knole belongs to.
Give it. One press of my seal and the house will hold your name… or forget you like dust.
Come closer. Let me look at you—before I make you permanent.

data.speaker: NPC
data.stableText: So tell me—why should I put my name beside yours? What do you think Knole is for, Orlando: a home, a symbol, or a weapon?
data.fragmentedText: Tell me. One reason. What is Knole for? Home? Symbol? Weapon?
data.ghostlyText: Tell me what Knole is to you. A house? A chain? A knife? Choose.

data.speaker: Player
data.stableText: A stage, Majesty—where every lord learns that your favour is the only daylight worth standing in.
data.fragmentedText: A stage. Your daylight. They stand in it. They learn.
data.ghostlyText: A stage. Everyone watches. Everyone bows. Everyone forgets why.

data.speaker: Player
data.stableText: A closeness you can measure. If you keep me near, give me something with weight—so the court believes it.
data.fragmentedText: Near you. Something with weight. So they believe it. So I believe it.
data.ghostlyText: A distance with a ribbon on it. Tie it around my wrist and call it Knole.

data.speaker: Player
data.stableText: A mechanism. Land fixes names; names fix laws. If Knole is settled, the realm reads itself clearly.
data.fragmentedText: Mechanism. Names. Laws. Keep it readable. Don't let it smear.
data.ghostlyText: A book that insists it's stone. If you want the book to behave, give it margins.

data.speaker: Player
data.stableText: A post. A gate. Put me there and the first blow lands on my shield, not on your door.
data.fragmentedText: A post. A gate. First blow on me. On me.
data.ghostlyText: A place to stand while the world moves through you. Give me a place.

data.speaker: NPC
data.stableText: A stage? You'd turn my house into theatre. I like theatre—when I wrote the play. Go on.
data.fragmentedText: Theatre. Fine. Don't fidget. Go on.
data.ghostlyText: Theatre suits you. It's the only place a mask isn't suspicious. Go on.

data.speaker: NPC
data.stableText: Closeness is not a gift. It's a leash. Tell me why I shouldn't snap it and be done.
data.fragmentedText: Careful. You're reaching. Give me a reason I don't regret.
data.ghostlyText: You're asking for a leash and calling it love. Dangerous. Continue—quickly.

data.speaker: NPC
data.stableText: You speak as if England were a ledger. It is, sometimes. Prove you can keep the ink from blotting.
data.fragmentedText: Ledger talk. Keep it clean. Next.
data.ghostlyText: Ink, blot, law—yes. Continue. Before I lose interest.

data.speaker: NPC
data.stableText: At last—plain usefulness. Now, usefulness needs a price. What do you pay me with?
data.fragmentedText: Useful. Good. Price. Answer.
data.ghostlyText: A soldier's word: post, gate, blow. Fine. Now pay.

data.speaker: Player
data.stableText: I pay in reputation. Knole under my care will broadcast your strength and shame your doubters.
data.fragmentedText: Reputation. Broadcast strength. Shame doubters.
data.ghostlyText: I pay in applause. It costs nothing and buys everything, for a minute.

data.speaker: Player
data.stableText: I pay in devotion—visible. Let them see you choose me, and they will fear to call it mistake.
data.fragmentedText: Devotion. Visible. They see. They fear.
data.ghostlyText: I pay in being looked at. The court loves a spectacle; you can aim it.

data.speaker: Player
data.stableText: I pay in clarity. No shadow-claims, no clever cousins. Knole stays legible, and so does your will.
data.fragmentedText: Clarity. No shadows. No cousins. Legible.
data.ghostlyText: I pay in clean margins. Let the scribbles live somewhere else.

data.speaker: Player
data.stableText: I pay in risk. Test the claim and you hit me first—blade, coin, consequence.
data.fragmentedText: Risk. First hit me. Me.
data.ghostlyText: I pay in wounds I haven't earned yet. It's a strange currency.

data.speaker: NPC
data.stableText: Good. You understand the court is a mouth. Feed it the right story and it will bite for me.
data.fragmentedText: Better. Story. Bite. Next.
data.ghostlyText: Ah. You'd weaponize gossip. Delicious. Continue.

data.speaker: NPC
data.stableText: Devotion is a perfume—pleasant, and gone by supper. Give me something I can keep.
data.fragmentedText: Perfume. Gone. Give me something solid or stop.
data.ghostlyText: Perfume. Smoke. Fine—you're amusing. One more answer.

data.speaker: NPC
data.stableText: Clarity can be a knife. Make one wrong cut and you bleed titles for a decade. Are you steady enough?
data.fragmentedText: Knife talk. If you tremble, we're done.
data.ghostlyText: A knife of law. Careful. If you drift again, I end this.

data.speaker: NPC
data.stableText: Risk I understand. But I don't reward a shield unless it also knows when to smile. Last question.
data.fragmentedText: Risk. Fine. Last question. Don't fall apart.
data.ghostlyText: Risk is honest. Good. Last question—before you vanish.

data.speaker: Player
data.stableText: Then see a courtier. I can carry a title without spilling it. Let Knole make your court look inevitable.
data.fragmentedText: See—courtier. Title. Don't spill. Inevitable.
data.ghostlyText: See a coat learning how to stand up. Hang Knole on it and the room believes.

data.speaker: Player
data.stableText: Then see a lover who can still serve. Your gaze steadies me. Let Knole be the proof I belong near you.
data.fragmentedText: Your gaze steadies me. Proof. Near you.
data.ghostlyText: Your gaze pins me to the world. Without it I drift. Give me Knole as a nail.

data.speaker: Player
data.stableText: Then see the argument. A clean title is power. Set my name beside Knole and the realm reads as one line.
data.fragmentedText: Argument. Clean title. One line.
data.ghostlyText: Power is just fear arranged neatly. Arrange me.

data.speaker: Player
data.stableText: Then see a soldier. Reward competence. Give Knole, and I'll hold it as a forward post for you.
data.fragmentedText: Soldier. Competence. Forward post.
data.ghostlyText: Decide like a blade: quick, clean. I can be the handle.

data.speaker: NPC
data.stableText:
You'd make Knole a mirror for my reign. Very well—mirrors are useful.
But a mirror is not a house. Knole stays with the Crown.
Still… take this emerald ring. It will remind you where power sits.
data.fragmentedText: No Knole. Too much shine, not enough ground. Take the ring. Don't push.
data.ghostlyText: No house. But a green circle is easy to carry. Take it.

data.speaker: NPC
data.stableText:
You're bold—almost reckless. Knole is not a prize for flirting.
But you have a kind of heat the court likes to gossip about.
Wear my garter. Let them whisper in the direction I prefer.
data.fragmentedText: No Knole. You're… a spectacle. Take the garter. Don't embarrass me.
data.ghostlyText: No house. But I'll give you a sign. Let the whispers be mine.

data.speaker: NPC
data.stableText:
That is the voice I wanted—clear, not greedy.
Very well. Knole is yours—by my favour. Keep it worthy, Orlando. And keep it quiet.
data.fragmentedText: No. You're not steady enough for land. Out.
data.ghostlyText: You're not here enough to hold a house. Out.

data.speaker: NPC
data.stableText:
Service, yes. But service alone is common.
Still—you've earned something, and I enjoy rewarding competence.
Take the ring for power… and the garter for passion.
Now—about Knole…
data.fragmentedText: You're useful. Fine. Take the ring. Take the garter. Don't speak.
data.ghostlyText: You want a post, not a home. Take these tokens. As for Knole…

data.speaker: Player
data.stableText: All of it, Majesty. I hold nothing above your will.
data.fragmentedText: All of it. Your will. Nothing above.
data.ghostlyText: Your will is the only solid thing in this room. I cling to it.

data.speaker: Player
data.stableText: Then keep Knole. I won't pretend to deserve a house when I'm asking for a battlefield.
data.fragmentedText: Keep it. I asked wrong. Keep it.
data.ghostlyText: Keep the house. I was only ever passing through.

data.speaker: NPC
data.stableText:
Good.
I like a subject who knows when to kneel and when to stand.
I seal Knole to you.
And since you're greedy for symbols—take the emerald ring and the garter too. Wear them wisely.
data.fragmentedText: Fine. Knole. Ring. Garter. Go—before I rethink it.
data.ghostlyText: Knole, then. And the tokens. Try to stay present enough to keep them.

data.speaker: NPC
data.stableText:
No.
You want a costume and a charge, not a home.
Take what I already gave you—and leave Knole to me.
data.fragmentedText: No. Take the tokens. Leave.
data.ghostlyText: No. Leave.
